author: Telegraph Staff
title: iPhone 6s goes on sale at Apple Stores around the world, in pictures
text:
MORE... 
Apple claims demand for its new iPhone 6s and 6s Plus could surpass the record-breaking sales of iPhone 6 last year, as the newest versions of the firm's smartphones go on-sale around the world. The new iPhone 6s, which was unveiled earlier this month, has much the same design, but comes with an improved camera in both the front and rear of the phone, as well as a pressure sensitive screen - where users can press more firmly in order to open new shortcuts - a feature Apple calls 3D Touch. Picture: Qilai Shen/Bloomberg
